Defines the maximum number of requests the backend can handle at a time. Probably fine to leave as-is but would depend on your node selector, model size, etc.
```
    concurrency=20,
```

Defines which GPUs to run your model on. Depends heavily on model size and architecture, for example if it's a gpt-oss variant you must have FA3 which means it can only run on hopper chips, so you would add `include=["h100", "h100_sxm", "h200"]`, otherwise you almost never need gpu_count=8 if it's not a massive model.  Use the minimum number of GPUs required to run your model, adjust min_vram_gb_per_gpu accordingly and/or specify an `include` list.
